<subSubSection id="C306789DFFCFFF9E6BB0FE88FCA9FDBB" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCFFF9E6BB0FE88FCA9FDBB" blockId="5.[151,1436,326,531]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
This is the second record of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6987FE88FCEAFEF7" box="[672,820,326,351]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and for the Arabian Peninsula. The first record of this species was from Abu Arish (southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E69B6FEA4FCF7FE2B" box="[657,809,362,387]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6846FEA4FB95FE2B" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[865,1099,362,387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6F7EFEA4FAB8FE2B" baseAuthorityName="Mayr" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1113,1382,362,387]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cerapachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitarsus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6F7EFEA4FAB8FE2B" box="[1113,1382,362,387]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Cerapachys longitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6A98FE40FE26FE0F" box="[447,504,398,423]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">India</collectingCountry>
and subsequently recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6850FE40FC6FFE0F" box="[887,945,398,423]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">UAE</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E68E7FE40FB3FFE0F" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T." box="[960,1249,398,423]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6877" refString="Collingwood, C. A., Agosti, D., Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T. (2011) Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 4, 405 - 474." type="journal article" year="2011">
Collingwood 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6F7AFE41FB49FE0F" box="[1117,1175,398,423]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6FD0FE41FAE4FE0F" box="[1271,1338,399,423]" name="Egypt" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Egypt</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6E6DFE40FF0AFE63" author="Sharaf, M. R." pageId="5" pageNumber="570" refId="ref8335" refString="Sharaf, M. R. (2006) Taxonomic and ecological studies on family Formicidae (Order: Hymenoptera) in Egypt including some protectorates with a study of some insect fauna associated with ant species. Ain Shams University, Faculty of Science, Entomology Department, Cairo (unpublished thesis), 340 pp." type="book" year="2006">Sharaf, 2006</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6BCBFE7CFEB3FE63" box="[236,365,434,459]" name="Philippines" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, North 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6AEDFE7CFDEDFE63" box="[458,563,434,459]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Australia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E695FFE7CFD14FE63" box="[632,714,434,459]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E69F1FE7CFD01FE63" bold="true" box="[726,735,434,459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">(</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E69F8FE7DFC3BFE63" author="Terayama, M. &amp; Kubota, S. &amp; Sakai, H. &amp; Kawazoe, A." box="[735,997,434,459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="35 - 38" refId="ref8948" refString="Terayama, M., Kubota, S., Sakai, H. &amp; Kawazoe, A. (1988) Rediscovery of Cerapachys sauteri Forel, 1913 (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Taiwan, with notes on the Taiwanese species of the genus Cerapachys. Bulletin of the Biogeographical Society of Japan, 43, 35 - 38." type="journal article" year="1988">
Terayama 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E687EFE7DFC48FE63" box="[857,918,434,459]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
, 1988
</bibRefCitation>
). At Rawdhat Khorim this species is considered rare, with only 
<specimenCount id="9D1AE09FFFCFFF9E6AE4FE18FDAFFE47" box="[451,625,470,495]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
. All are alate males, three attracted to a light trap and one collected by a pitfall trap. They were collected in April, October and November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
